[normal]Unvalidated
[normal] examination results 
[normal] 
[normal]Except for 16-19 academies which are inspected under the Common Inspection Framework for Further Education Learning and Skills
[normal] Figures are for primary and secondary academies where deprivation has been classified. 
[normal]Deprivation is b
[normal]ased on the Income Deprivation Affecting Children Index (IDACI) 2010. The deprivation of a provider is based on the mean of the deprivation indices associated with the home post codes of the pupils attending the school rather than the location of the schoo
[normal]l itself. The schools are divided into five equal groups (quintiles) that are labelled from ‘most deprived’ to ‘least deprived’
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]This includes f
[normal]ree 
[normal]s
[normal]chools, University Technical Colleges and 
[normal]s
[normal]tudio 
[normal]s
[normal]chools
[normal]All academ
[normal]ies, including free schools, have a l
[normal]egal status as
[normal] independent schools and must meet the requirements of the Independent Schools Register. Those academies which acquire academy status under the Academies Act 2010 are deemed to have met those requirements upon opening and, therefore, do not u
[normal]ndergo pre-registration inspections
